<subSubSection id="C358655E86156B33FA9487B9F826F3E6" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586156B33FA9487B9F826F3E6" blockId="7.[1307,2293,2919,3197]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
Remarks. The present specimens resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686156B33F7B787B9F9BDF3B9" authority="Waagen (1880)" authorityName="Waagen" authorityYear="1880" class="Gastropoda" family="Euphemitidae" genus="Warthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786156B33F7B787B9F76EF46F" box="[2159,2292,3021,3060]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Warthia</emphasis>
Waagen (1880)
</taxonomicName>
in having a convolute spire and in lack of ornamentation, but differs in that 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686156B33F833805DF7E9F3D4" authorityName="Waagen" authorityYear="1880" box="[2027,2163,3113,3151]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euphemitidae" genus="Warthia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786156B33F833805DF7E9F3D4" box="[2027,2163,3113,3151]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Warthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a rounded margin and short, wide slit.
</paragraph>
